{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Line a cake tin (Ø 20 cm) and grease with oil then set aside.","Place Parmesan, bread and parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>Turbo\/2 sec\/3 times<b>. Tip out and set aside.","Place water in mixing bowl and place Varoma dish into position. Weigh potatoes into Varoma dish and steam <b>25 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Check potatoes are cooked, if not steam <b>2-5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Set Varoma aside and discard steaming water. Place cooked potatoes, eggs, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then mix to combine <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Spread half of breadcrumb mixture onto base of prepared cake tin, then place half of potato mixture on top. Cover with a layer of ham followed by a layer of mozzarella. Top with remaining potato mixture, then finish with remaining breadcrumbs. Bake in oven for 35-45 minutes (170°C) until well browned. Serve warm or cold with a salad."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["olive oil, for greasing","50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces","60 g bread","1 small handful fresh parsley (approx. 5 g)","1000 g water, for steaming","1000 g potatoes, peeled, diced (2 cm)","4 large eggs","1 - 1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","2 pinches ground black pepper","100 g ham, cooked, diced","220 g mozzarella, sliced (5 mm)"]}],"id":"r84808","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-RVlFixxO_Hg\/XZWZ_M9sfII\/AAAAAAAAeUg\/cy6xG8bHDmY8-HcRAlVRjDEb11U_3uGuACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_s2KjbPuXhKEjOWQL.png","title":"Napoli Potato Cake","publishedAt":"2015-08-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"21.9 g","fat":"15.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"33.4 g","calories":"1497 kJ \/ 358 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cake tin (Ø 20 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["A traditional dish of Naples, this potato cake works well as a main course or side dish or even cold for a picnic."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}